node.text:
Recently, we have seen an increase in demand for rental real estate. Unusual and unique projects are particularly popular. More and more people around the world are abandoning the idea of buying their own home in favor of the opportunity to choose housing to their liking, the opportunity to freely change it at any time. Emotions that a new house can evoke and impression that it can make are of the most inportance for them. And when those feelings begin to weaken, people simply change their house for a new one. Therefore, I would like to ask you what is your choice: to have your own house or to give up owning in favor of more vivid sensations? And why?

node.text:
The main idea of the concept is that any architect, designer or artist should go far beyond the patterns prevailing in your field. The ability of the creator to look at things from a different angle, I believe, is a pillar of modern art. There are many climatic zones around the world where there is no need for large-scale construction. And we could build something lighter and less expensive.

node.text:
Jeñil-house by @alex_nerovnya 

You will be able to rent this spacious house with a swimming pool in Kazakhstan soon. Due to the design features, being inside this house, you will feel the complete absence of walls. And you will fully enjoy the incredibly beautiful views of the mountains of Kazakhstan. The layout concept of the house provides a spacious living room and two cozy bedrooms. This house is equally suitable for a quiet family holiday, and for a fun holiday with a large company.

node.text:
Wildfires, droughts, floods. Nature does not hint, it says directly: I am done with you. We should have acted yesterday, and I made a decision that I should have made a long time ago. From now on, I will donate 10% of my income to the restoration of forests in Siberia. I encourage everyone to join me. I also promise that all my new projects will be made of completely recyclable materials. 

My new project stord house is a sketch of a modular building in an eco-complex being developed in Kazakhstan. In the living room of this one-story house, a two-light space is created thanks to an additional roof module.
Stord house by @alex_nerovnya

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Alexander Nerovnya in Moscow Oblast. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Dear friends, we have been pretty busy lately with a series of new architectural projects in Europe, USA, Asia and Russia. 

We'll try to keep up our Instagram posting schedule, starting with this little tree house concept, inspired by our recent trip to a number of mountain resorts in Kazakhstan. 

It's a tiny glamping cabin, consisting of a single bedroom with a skylight-style transparent roof - an ideal wilderness retreat for lovers.

Its area is just 7 square meters, but a large amount of facade glazing would allow the visitors to keep constant visual connection with the surrounding natural environment.

Would you be excited to stay in this little tree house with a significant other or alone? Share your deepest glamping-related desires with us in the comments below!
